      <p class="alert-title" title="Dynamics 365 ERP Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server now generally available (GA)">Dynamics 365 ERP Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server now generally available (GA)</p>
      <p>February 18, 2026</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-link" data-json="[{&quot;Description&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;A major milestone for agentic ERP is here: The new Dynamics 365 ERP Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server makes Dynamics 365 the most agent-ready ERP on the market. The server is now GA, giving partners and customers access to 650,000+ ERP actions and unlocking real, scalable agent scenarios partners can lead with today.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;With Dynamics 365 ERP MCP Server, partners and customers can now build intelligent, reliable agents that read, reason, and act across Dynamics 365 Finance and Supply Chain—without brittle integrations or custom plumbing. MCP provides a standardized, open protocol for contextualizing ERP data and actions for LLMs, giving agents native access to the full depth of their ERP, including customizations.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Enabling partners to lead with concrete agent scenarios&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Dynamics 365 now provides full, standardized, production-ready agent access across Finance, Supply Chain, HR, and Project Operations. With additional solutions like ERP Analytics MCP in Public Preview and ERP Commerce MCP in Private Preview, Microsoft is the only vendor delivering a unified agent framework across operations and insights. These combined capabilities enable partners to build and deploy agents that can do almost anything a user can do within Dynamics 365.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Call to Action&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead with Agentic ERP:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive customer conversations with agentic ERP by showing how MCP unlocks real agent capabilities today and enables advanced analytics.\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3P Agents:&lt;/strong&gt; Promote your latest &lt;a href=\&quot;https://marketplace.microsoft.com/en-us/search/products?search=ERP%20MCP&amp;page=1\&quot;&gt;D365 ERP MCP partner-built agents on Microsoft Marketplace&lt;/a&gt; to bring into your customer conversations.\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Resources&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\&quot;https://msbulkcomm.microsoft.com/h/i/dzy3kGN6/c1nn4HRR?url=https://community.dynamics.com/blogs/post/?postid=76cf837d-05da-f011-8544-7ced8d1ab86c\&quot;&gt;“Accelerating AI agent development” Tech Talk&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\&quot;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/copilot/copilot-mcp\&quot;&gt;Use Model Context Protocol for finance and operations apps - Finance &amp; Operations&lt;/a&gt; (Microsoft Learn)\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\&quot;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/copilot/extend-copilot\&quot;&gt;Extend Copilot capabilities in finance and operations apps&lt;/a&gt; (Microsoft Learn)\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\&quot;https://msbulkcomm.microsoft.com/h/i/dzy3kBz4/c1nn4HRR?url=https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics-365/blog/business-leader/2025/05/20/the-autonomous-enterprise-how-generative-ai-is-reshaping-business-applications/\&quot;&gt;ERP MCP blog post&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&quot;,&quot;FileLink&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;FileLinkVideo&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;FileModifiedDate&quot;:&quot;2026-02-17&quot;,&quot;FileName&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Icon&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;ImportFilePath&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;IsActive&quot;:&quot;No&quot;,&quot;IsProtected&quot;:&quot;No&quot;,&quot;Link&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;LinkTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Owner&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Paragraph&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;RowID&quot;:&quot;5775282a-7d8e-409a-95b1-b0bc638041d6&quot;,&quot;VideoThumbnail&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Description&quot;}]"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="alert-card">
    <div class="alert-header-vertical">
      <div class="tag-line">
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        
        
        
      </div>


      <p class="alert-title" title="Growing with agents: How to tap into the agentic AI opportunity">Growing with agents: How to tap into the agentic AI opportunity</p>
      <p>November 6, 2025</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-link" data-json="[{&quot;Description&quot;:&quot;\n&lt;p&gt;Microsoft is focused on helping partners embrace agentic AI for the massive opportunity it presents in terms of both customer transformation and business growth. This technology is going to be mandatory to maintain competitive advantage for companies moving forward but figuring out where to start can be challenging given the speed with which new features are being released.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;We have been holding conversations with partners about what building an agentic AI-focused business from the ground up looks like.&lt;strong&gt;&#160;KiZAN, a Microsoft AI Cloud Partner with numerous Solutions Partner designations and specializations located in Cincinnati, OH, is one of the partners that we&#39;ve been speaking with, and their deep engagement and investment in driving AI adoption broadly with its customers has yielded important insights on early customer engagement.&lt;/strong&gt;&#160;One of these engagements – focused on a law firm that has a large number of healthcare-related cases – highlights some of the most significant steps in helping drive customer success in this new and rapidly growing area, and I wanted to share these learnings with our broader partner community.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Start with a high impact problem&lt;/strong&gt;&#160;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;To prove the value of agents, it is important to identify where you can drive the biggest impact for customers. KiZAN has a lot of experience in the legal industry, so it reasoned that the natural workflows of this document-rich environment would lend itself well to agentic solutions, especially in the area of deposition transcription summarization. When the partner pitched the idea to one of its oldest clients, the team encountered some surprises.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\&quot;I was really hoping to get thirty minutes of his time, but he ended up talking to us for four hours,\&quot; said Tom Cantrell, Director of Product Services at KiZAN. During this marathon session, the customer shared that while the deposition transcription would be useful, it wasn&#39;t really that exciting. Instead, a more critical challenge the firm faced was staffing its healthcare cases with nurse paralegals. These individuals have specialized skillsets that allow them to review medical records and create summaries, timelines, and some analysis on what those records hold in the context of a legal matter or case. Nurse paralegals are hard to find and their case workloads can take months, which potentially limits the amount of casework that the firm can take on in the medical industry.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;So KiZAN quickly pivoted to address this critical pain point. \&quot;You have to invest in your customer so that you can understand their desired outcomes. You can&#39;t do that in a black box – it&#39;s the customer&#39;s voice that is the most important,\&quot; said Tom.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Make sure you pick a client that is willing to iterate&#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Speed is one of the most exciting factors of agentic AI. The ability to use Microsoft Copilot Studio to create agents quickly can be a powerful tool – but only if you have a customer that is willing to provide continuous feedback so that this rapid development delivers the right outcomes.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;KiZAN asked for one of the legal firm&#39;s simpler past cases to build a prototype solution. The team was given a case with raw medical records and gold standard outputs that the nurse paralegals had produced. The team opened up Copilot Studio and started to build out a workflow that prompted for records and managed each piece of the process in a chat conversation, including uploading and processing records, and delivering analysis. \&quot;Our goal was to move very quickly to build something, get feedback, build something again, show something, get more feedback, and so on,\&quot; said Tom.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;When shown the prototype, the customer was very excited about the speed of the solution, since summaries and analyses could be created in minutes. But it turned out the case the customer had provided was an outlier. Typically, there are hundreds of documents or even tens of thousands of documents. KiZAN realized quickly that the prototype wouldn&#39;t scale in its current form, and the partner needed to go back to the drawing board.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\&quot;Given this is such a new area of technology, you want to make sure your first set of clients are very open-minded, adaptable, and willing to work with you through these cases and iterations,\&quot; said Lee Hovermale, Strategic Advisor to the CEO at KiZAN. \&quot;Because all other things aside, if you don&#39;t have that client who&#39;s willing to sit at the table with you and spend time, you&#39;re not going to be able to deliver customer value.\&quot;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Low code and pro code aren&#39;t exclusive&#160;&#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;KiZAN realized that to scale the existing solution it needed to add a robust document-management capability, which would require technologies outside of the low-code portfolio. \&quot;We made a promising start, but when you hear requirements like the need to summarize 19,000 pages in a document where there are doctor&#39;s notes written on top, we knew the initial chat experience wasn&#39;t going to be able to manage on its own,\&quot; said Tom.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;KiZAN switched from a simple SharePoint backend to SharePoint Embedded to provide a richer customer UI experience. This new front end was designed to handle the continual input of documents as they are made available to the legal team over several months, and integration with Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat maintained a chat-based experience for uploading and managing documents.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;When it came to higher-level analysis, the team moved to Azure AI Foundry as its foundation solution. However, they continued to rely on Copilot Studio to build out the custom agent. \&quot;It doesn&#39;t need to be either or – there are things you get in Copilot Studio that make no sense for us to ignore the value of or try to build on our own. Where we want to focus and be more deterministic, we&#39;ll use pro-dev tools. But with the Microsoft stack we get the best of both worlds – which is going to help us deliver this next iteration of the prototype in just eight weeks,\&quot; said Tom.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Make agents standard operating practice for your organization&#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;When it comes to direct advice to other partners, both Tom and Lee agreed on the most important practice for partners: building an AI mindset. This is as true for partner teams as it is for customers.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\&quot;I live in Copilot Studio, live in the tool set, use it every day,\&quot; said Tom. \&quot;You need to make it clear that this tool set is not for three developers sitting on your Modern Work team. This is a technology that we want everybody from operations to sales to marketing to our professional services teams using.\&quot;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\&quot;You really have to dedicate a new mindset to AI-first for everything. We&#39;re often working with attorneys or paralegals who have been in the field for decades and are very disciplined about their processes. You need to help them navigate the journey and be willing to be open to what these new technologies will offer even if there is a bit of frustration, because this is the future,\&quot; concluded Lee.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&#39;s next&#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;We&#39;ll check in with KiZAN next quarter to see how this solution has progressed and what additional learnings the team can share. In the meantime, make sure to&#160;&lt;a href=\&quot;https://cloudpartners.transform.microsoft.com/practices/modern-work/copilot\&quot; target=\&quot;_blank\&quot;&gt;check out the resources we have available for getting started on building your agentic AI practice&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;FileLink&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;FileLinkVideo&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;FileModifiedDate&quot;:&quot;2025-11-07&quot;,&quot;FileName&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Icon&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;ImportFilePath&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;IsActive&quot;:&quot;No&quot;,&quot;IsProtected&quot;:&quot;No&quot;,&quot;Link&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;LinkTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Owner&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;Paragraph&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;RowID&quot;:&quot;73216657-a1bd-4abc-a030-47045c022939&quot;,&quot;VideoThumbnail&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Description&quot;}]"></div>
  </div>
  
</div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const alerts = document.querySelectorAll(".bottom-link");

    alerts.forEach(linkContainer => {
      const rawJson = linkContainer.getAttribute("data-json");
      if (!rawJson) return;

      try {
        const blocks = JSON.parse(rawJson);

        blocks.forEach(block => {
          if (block.type === "Link") {
            const isProtected = String(block.IsProtected).toLowerCase() === 'true' ? 1 : 0;

            const anchor = document.createElement("a");
            anchor.href = "#";
            anchor.className = "card-link";
            anchor.dataset.href = block.Link;
            anchor.onclick = (event) => SecureLinkHandler.handleProtectedNavigation(event, anchor, isProtected);
            anchor.oncontextmenu = (event) => false;

            anchor.textContent = block.LinkTitle || "Read the blog";

            const svgHTML = `
            <svg width="6" height="10" viewBox="0 0 6 10" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M0.646447 0.137169C0.451184 0.332431 0.451184 0.649014 0.646447 0.844276L4.79289 4.99072L0.646447 9.13717C0.451185 9.33243 0.451185 9.64901 0.646447 9.84428C0.841709 10.0395 1.15829 10.0395 1.35355 9.84428L5.85355 5.34428C6.04882 5.14901 6.04882 4.83243 5.85355 4.63717L1.35355 0.137169C1.15829 -0.0580929 0.841709 -0.0580929 0.646447 0.137169Z" fill="#0F6CBD"></path>
            </svg>
          `;
            anchor.insertAdjacentHTML("beforeend", svgHTML);

            linkContainer.appendChild(anchor);
          }
        });

        linkContainer.removeAttribute("data-json");

      } catch (err) {
        console.error("Error parsing JSON for link container:", err);
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .alert-card {
    background-color: white;
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    /* box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05) 0px 4px 8px; */
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    min-height: 145px;
  }

  .alert-header-vertical {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-top: 5px;
    row-gap: 6px;
  }

  .tag-line {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .badge {
    padding: 4px 10px;
    font-size: 10px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    font-weight: 600;
    background-color: #091F2C;
    color: #ffffff;
    display: inline-block;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .alert-header-vertical .alert-title {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #272727;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }

  .alert-card p {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #707070;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .bottom-link {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .bottom-link .card-link {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #0f6cbd;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    text-decoration: none !important;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .bottom-link .card-link svg {
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-top: 3px;
